#REMARK SUMMARY
TITLE	ketoreductase-enoylreductase didomain
BIOISIS_ID	ZGDWKP
EXP_DESCRIPTION	To investigate whether the conformation of the Spn(KR+ER)2 didomain in solution is similar to that observed in the crystal structure, SAXS was performed. The experimental scattering curve closely matched the scattering curve predicted by the program CRYSOL for the Spn(KR+ER)2 monomer from the crystal structure. The radius of gyration determined from the SAXS data through the Guinier approximation (29.5 Å) and through GNOM (30.0 Å) matches that calculated from the Spn(KR+ER)2 crystal structure (30.2 Å). The ab initio molecular envelope generated from the SAXS data by the program DAMMIF indicates a compact two-domain structure consistent with the Spn(KR+ER)2 crystal structure.
SOURCE_LOCATION	The Sealy Center for Structural Biology,  Rigaku BioSAXS-1000 on a FRE+DW
PUBLICATION	Manuscript is being accepted
